Psalm 13

2 How lóng, O Lórd? Will you forgét me foréver?
How lóng will you híde your fáce from mé?
3 How lóng must I bear gríef in my sóul,
have sórrow in my héart all day lóng?
How lóng shall my énemy preváil over mé?

4 Lóok, ánswer me, Lórd my Gód!
Give líght to my éyes lest I fáll asleep in déath;
5 lest my énemy sáy, ``Í have overcóme him";
lest my fóes rejóice when they sée me fáll.

6 As for mé, I trúst in your mérciful lóve.
Let my héart rejóice in yóur salvátion.
7 I will síng to the Lórd who has been bóuntiful with mé.
I will sing psálms to the náme of the Lórd Most Hígh.
